race.comment: MOXIE (14) ran eighth in her second-up effort over 1400m at Ellerslie from a wide gate. She was the gamest of thirds there fresh up, and her trainer Ken Harrison does a great job with his small team. She is on top here for us. BIG WAVE (4) showed a lot of courage when finishing third last time over 1400m at Ellerslie, ending up a length and a half off the winner. He cops a wide gate here, but likes to race handy, and he has the toughness to match his good record. Stick with him. SHE'S UNTOUCHABLE (16) hasn't won for a while but will be at her peak fitness now after a game fourth last start as the favourite over 1400m at Ellerslie 18 days ago. She has a superior gate, and also drops 5kg in weight here. Don't risk her. PEERLESS (9) resumes after a win over 1600m at Ellerslie five-and-a-half months ago. He has a quiet trial recently, and his stable is running hot. Include in all combinations.
